@node "GuideBrowser" "GuideBorwser"
@next "L'auteur"
@prev "Légalité"

      @{fg shadow}@{bg shine}GuideBrowser@{fg text}@{bg back} is made of two parts :

            @{fg shadow}@{bg shine}GuideBrowser,@{fg text}@{bg back} @{u}the software@{uu}

      With this executable, you will create a new AmigaGuide document.
      You give as parameters a @{i}CHEMIN,@{ui} a @{i}NOM DE FICHIER TEXTE@{ui} and
      finally a @{i}NOM DE FICHIER GUIDE@{ui} :

          @{bg shadow} @{bg back} the @{i}CHEMIN@{ui} corresponds to the directory which contains the Guide
            or Doc (etc.) files, these files will have a direct access created ;

          @{bg shadow} @{bg back} the @{i}NOM DE FICHIER TEXTE@{ui} is the name of the file where each lines
            corresponds to a path to a Guide or Doc file ;

          @{bg shadow} @{bg back} the @{i}NOM DE FICHIER GUIDE@{ui} is the name (and the path) of the new Guide file,
            which will be created and which will provide a direct access to your documents.






            @{fg shadow}@{bg shine}CreateGuideBorwser,@{fg text}@{bg back} @{u}the script@{uu}

      This script generates automatically the list of your Guide, Doc, ReadMe,
      aso. files contained in a directory.
      It takes as parameters a @{i}CHEMIN,@{ui} a @{i}FICHIER TEXTE@{ui} and a @{i}FICHIER GUIDE@{ui},
      as before :

          @{bg shadow} @{bg back} the @{i}CHEMIN@{ui} is the one of the directory containing the Guide, etc. files ;

          @{bg shadow} @{bg back} a @{i}FICHIER TEXTE@{ui} is the name (and the path) of the file, which will contain
            the list of the documents which you want a direct access ;

          @{bg shadow} @{bg back} the @{i}FICHIER GUIDE@{ui} is the name (and the path) of the new Guide file, which will
            be created.








            @{fg shadow}@{bg shine}CreateGuideBorwser,@{fg text}@{bg back} @{u}the test@{uu}

      I think an example will be better than a long speech (@{" it's without danger " link "Légalité" 0}) : try
      the command line below (be in the directory containing GuideBrowser and CreateGuideBrowser) :

            @{fg fill}CreateGuideBrowser HELP: T:GuideBrowser.tmp RAM:GuideBrowser.Guide@{fg text}

      and have look to the file GuideBorwser.Guide :

            @{fg fill}MultiView RAM:GuideBrowser.Guide@{fg text}

     @{" What do you think about it ? " link "L'auteur" 0}
@endnode

